<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF4FFCCFF02FDABFF257727" blockId="8.[130,777,567,1007]" box="[132,207,567,593]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF4FFCCFF02FDCBFE447687" blockId="8.[130,777,567,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF4FFCCFF02FDCBFE9B7719" author="LECOMTE H." box="[132,369,599,625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" pagination="99 - 121" refId="ref13173" refString="LECOMTE H. 1928 a. - Ebenacees nouvelles de l'Indochine. Notulae Systematicae 4 (4): 99 - 121. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 6463259" type="journal article" year="1928">Lecomte (1928a: 104)</bibRefCitation>
cited three collections from 
<collectingCountry id="F30C8BBDFFF4FFCCFD1AFDCBFD067719" box="[668,748,599,625]" name="Vietnam" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Annam</collectingCountry>
in the protologue: 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFEB5FDEAFE2777F8" box="[307,461,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 10375</emphasis>
from Dent du Tigre, 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFD3DFDEAFF2077D8" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 11202</emphasis>
from Dang co pat, and 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFE5FFD0AFD8C77D8" box="[473,614,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 1108</emphasis>
from Dangtri, all in Phanrang Province. Several sheets of 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFDECFD2AFCE277B8" box="[618,776,694,720]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 10375</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFF33FD4AFEBB7798" box="[181,337,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 11202</emphasis>
have been located at NY, P and SING. The collection 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFEA7FD6AFE417678" box="[289,427,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 1108</emphasis>
, held at P, is not a 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF4FFCCFDE9FD6BFD3B7678" box="[623,721,759,784]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFDE9FD6BFD3B7678" box="[623,721,759,784]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Diospyros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and none of the label data match in any way the protologue. We found, however, three sheets of 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFE43FCAAFDB07638" box="[453,602,822,848]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 11018</emphasis>
at P, determined as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF4FFCCFF27FCCAFEBC7607" box="[161,342,854,879]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eugenii">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFF27FCCAFEBC7607" box="[161,342,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Diospyros eugenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Lecomte, with matching label data, and each annotated ‘11018 et non 1108’. Among the three gatherings, we designate here as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF4FFCCFD89FC09FD9B76C7" box="[527,625,917,943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">lectotype</typeStatus>
the specimen 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF4FFCCFF03FC29FEC976A7" box="[133,291,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="121">Poilane 10375</emphasis>
(P[P00721514]), which includes a detailed drawing of the male flower.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
